result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer C Valdez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Jennifer C Valdez in court with attorney Nicole Williams Buttery.  Kristi Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty. Count #1 is dismissed and read in. The Defendant is sentenced as follows:  FINE: $259.30  to be paid at  $39.53 per month commencing 12/1/15 or serve 9 days jail consecutive for failure to pay.    Court waives the DNA sample.    DNA Surcharge: $200.00. (to be part of payment plan on fine) Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees, obtain high school diploma and no new criminal law violations.

Request for adjournment filed by plaintiff.
Reviewed by Judge Aprahamian - to be addressed at status hearing.
Filed by the State. Witness list attached.

Defendant Jennifer C Valdez in court (one hour late) with attorney Nicole Williams Buttery.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense requests another date. Defendant is going to take a six week course for treatment. Court will set the matter for a jury status/jury trial date.  Jury status hearing scheduled for November 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial - 12 person scheduled for November 10, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on September 4, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jennifer C Valdez in court with attorney Nicole Williams Buttery.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense received an updated offer. Defendant needs to complete anger management and requests another date. Court will give a date in 60 days for plea/sentencing.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 4, 2015 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Jennifer C Valdez in court with attorney Nicole Williams-Buttery.  Kevin M. Osborne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defense requests another date in 45 days. Defense has not received discovery on this matter yet. Court grants request. Defense to let the court know on the next date how this matter will proceed - plea or trial.  Hearing scheduled for July 6, 2015 at 09:00 am.
Defendant to have no contact with victim/witness or her residence if the victim is at the residence.
